<HEADLINE> Solar Energy Probed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A three-men team said that the
Uganda government is considering to intruduce solar energy to the
rural areas, "the New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The team now is carrying a market servey for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
The team demonstrated to members of the district local
councils the solar equipment used in tapping solar electricity
which included the bulbs, the panels which store solar energy,
the solar-operated laterns and battery.
</P>
<P>
The team consisted of United Nations Development Program
official in charge of global environment facility Steve Hirch,
Chairman of all solar companies in Uganda John Semanda, and the
principal energy officer in the Mministry of Natural Resources
Livingstone Bangi.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is a fuel poverty-striken country. It consumed imported
oil. enditem

